FBIS4-103 "drafr063_e_94008" FBIS-AFR-94-063 Daily Report 30 Mar 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Paper Rejects Nigeria's Bid for Permanent UN Seat Paper Rejects Nigeria's Bid for Permanent UN Seat AB3003182294 Lagos Voice of Nigeria in English 1030 GMT 30 Mar 94 AB3003182294 Lagos Voice of Nigeria English BFN [From the press review] [Text] The DAILY TIMES rejects Nigeria's efforts to have a permanent seat at the United Nations Security Council as it has been making conscious efforts to have a place for Africa in the supreme organ of the UN. Reporting further on this move, the paper quotes Nigeria's minister of external affairs as stating that it will give all the regions in the world equal and fairer presentation.
